  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n<!--A clear and concise description of what the bug is and steps to reproduce it.-->\r\nIf I stop the beacon after some time and restart (in this case, it was after having to restart due to #1509 ), I notice that some of the epochs that are listed in beacon chain explorer (https://beaconcha.in/epochs) that are marked as finalized are not shown as justified or finalized while running our beacon node.\r\n\r\nFor example, https://beaconcha.in/epoch/2297\r\nEpoch 2297 is shown as finalized, but if you look at this log, you will not see it listed as justified or finalized (this is the same log I attached in #1509 )\r\n[testlog.txt](https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/files/5171819/testlog.txt)\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n<!--A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen.-->\r\nShow all justified and finalized epochs in the logs.",
